Flames shot out of Thassalin's throat as the huge Thracian set a particular woodland area in bounds and then circled over it to recognize movements. Notably, the eerie screeching behind him ceased as he slowed down. Thassalin had forgotten the passengers on his back.
“What's this, Tenuk, you've turned into a Thracian before?”
“If I fly myself, it's completely different from being suddenly lifted up by a huge pink dragon!”
“It wasn't that bad, was it, Kayel?”
Kayel didn't seem to agree with Nyssis' opinion. He looked less black than usual and his claws had sunk so deep into Thassalin's back that the Thracian was bleeding. However, Thassalin seemed to be unbothered by this. Nevertheless, he had realized that he had scared his new friends and landed on a clearing.
"I'M SORRY, BUT I HAD SOMETHING BURNT. I HAD TO TAKE CARE OF IT!"
"But did you have to drag us along too?", growled Tenuk, as he climbed off Thassalin's back and slid down onto its tail. "And we left Retvik behind! Our big, strong warrior was abandoned! How is he supposed to catch up to us?"
"He'll think of something…", growled Nyssi. "Retvik isn't the fastest, but he's not stupid."
"True, but can Retvik drive?"
Nyssi winked and turned back to Tenuk. "Of course, he can drive."
“Have you ever seen Retvik drive a vehicle? He doesn’t have a truck like you, and I have never seen him drive a nice small car like Kayel's either. Besides, he only started taking the car for work because you always drive us. He only has his bicycle.”
Thunderous laughter interrupted them. Thassalin suddenly seemed to find something absolutely hilarious, but no one knew what he was laughing at. It took a bit too long for Thassalin to calm down.
“I APOLOGIZE, BUT I PRESENTED YOUR MASSIVE FRIEND ON SUCH A SMALL BIKE IN RUSTHAN FOR CHILDREN. IT WAS KILLING ME! I WISH I HAD SOME KIND OF TELEPATHY. A WONDERFUL PRESENTATION! ONE THAT I CANNOT SHARE!”
Kayel chuckled, thinking that he could guess what was going on in Thassalin's head. “Yeah, that's true. But what did you smell, and why did you suddenly take off?”
Thassalin grunted, rose up and vanished. When he returned after a short time, he threw something lifeless at Nyssi's feet. It was an Orothrack, a very rare, gold-white dragon-like creature. But it was missing its head. “ANOTHER DEAD ONE. I HEAR YOUR SCREAMS. I SMELL YOUR BLOOD. SOMETHING IS URGEING ME TO PROTECT AND HUNT. LIKE YISINI ORDERS. THEY ARE CLOSE BY.”
The mighty Thraki froze suddenly. Nyssi and Kayel also froze and looked attentively at a gap in the clearing. Something Great and Black was staring at them and snarling. Whatever it was, it spread out two enormous pairs of wings and shot towards Thassalin without caring about the three smaller beings between them. Kayel and Tenuk could just barely take cover, but Nyssi was caught up and almost thrown at Thassalin.
Thassalin reacted to this attack by seizing Nyssi and hurling him with his incredibly long and skilled tail onto his back, before he himself took off into the air. The black, double-winged creature pursued them at high speed.
Kayel snorted in annoyance, while he took his rifle from his back and opened a pouch containing a cartridge belt. He hung the belt over his chest, but quickly realized that Nyssi, the Thraki, and the monster were out of sight.
“Hey, Tenuk, could you transform into something that can fly?” asked Kayel.
“You want to pursue them?”
“Yes, of course!”
“But… One of them is a huge monster!”
“Yes and? I'm standing here with a high-caliber gun in my hand and could shoot at it immediately. But, well, how should I say – I would have to see it in order to hit it.”
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to have more space. With a soft, painful grunt, Tenuk's body stretched out, his fur turned to scales and his arms to wings. He quickly transformed into a normal, sky-blue Thraki, but his eyes remained red.
“Get on.”
Tenuk now looked like an ordinary Thracian, but he had a proper scute shield running along his back. Conveniently, a pair of spines had also grown on his back, which Kayel could hold onto. It took a bit too long for Tenuk to succeed in taking off, but once in the air, he quickly oriented himself and tried to pick up the pursuit.
Tenuk and Kayel soon realized that they were not alone. A second dark being shot up under them, and Tenuk could only narrowly avoid a collision.
„Is that probably the other terrifying giant monster that Lanex was afraid of?“ Kayel furrowed his brow. He tried to shoot at the second beast, missed, and reloaded quickly.
Tenuk did not respond. He was too busy concentrating on flying towards Nyssi and Thassalin, although the other beast was pursuing them. Kayel turned unsteadily around to keep the monster in sight. The fact that it was pursuing them was a benefit for Kayel, as he could more easily aim and fire. Two shots went through the upper wings of the beast. It let out a scream of pain and sank back under the trees. Kayel was not sure if it was still following them, but it would certainly not be able to keep up with them.
A good bit ahead of them, Nyssi was clinging desperately, while Thassalin was thrashing about and spewing flames at the blackened monster. The creature was definitely wounded. It seemed furious but not ready to give up. The fireballs seemed to have the desired effect. As Thassalin stretched out, Nyssi took the opportunity to draw her own weapon, a good old shotgun. It may not be the first choice, but perhaps the buckshot would scare the black beast off.
